"title": "2027: Jesus Christ, grace and mercy of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "2027",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The qualities of Jesus Christ by which he is compassionate, accepting and generous. In his ministry, Christ demonstrates these qualities towards those whom he encounters. Believers should model themselves upon Jesus Christ in this respect.</p>\n<h2>The grace and mercy of God made known in Jesus Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:14\">JHN 1:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:16-John1:17\">JHN 1:16–1:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:40\">LUK 2:40</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:52\">LUK 2:52</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor8:9\">2CO 8:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:11\">TIT 2:11</a> <em>Jesus Christ shows the grace of God in his life.</em></p>\n<h2>Grace and mercy in the ministry of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ responds to pleas for mercy</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:27-Matt9:30\">MAT 9:27–9:30</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:22\">MAT 15:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:29-Matt20:34\">MAT 20:29–20:34</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:46-Mark10:52\">MRK 10:46–10:52</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:35-Luke18:42\">LUK 18:35–18:42</a></p>\n<h3>His teaching reflects his grace and mercy</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:35-Luke6:36\">LUK 6:35–6:36</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos6:6\">HOS 6:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:12-Matt6:15\">MAT 6:12–6:15</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:4\">LUK 11:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:10-Matt9:13\">MAT 9:10–9:13</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:15-Mark2:17\">MRK 2:15–2:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:29-Luke5:32\">LUK 5:29–5:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:21-Matt18:35\">MAT 18:21–18:35</a> <em>the parable of the unmerciful servant</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:30-Luke10:37\">LUK 10:30–10:37</a> <em>the parable of the good Samaritan</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:32\">EPH 4:32</a></p>\n<h2>Grace and mercy in relation to salvation</h2>\n<h3>The grace of Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:11\">ACT 15:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:24\">ROM 3:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:15\">ROM 5:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:4-Eph2:5\">EPH 2:4–2:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:8\">EPH 2:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:9\">2TI 1:9</a></p>\n<h3>The mercy of Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:34\">LUK 23:34</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:2\">MAT 9:2</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:3-Mark2:5\">MRK 2:3–2:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:18-Luke5:20\">LUK 5:18–5:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:37-Luke7:38\">LUK 7:37–7:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:48\">LUK 7:48</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:6\">ROM 5:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:15\">ROM 5:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim1:13-1Tim1:14\">1TI 1:13–1:14</a> <em>Paul speaks about his persecution of the Christians prior to his conversion experience.</em></p>\n<h3>Eternal life is a gift of grace and mercy</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:21\">ROM 5:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:23\">ROM 6:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus3:7\">TIT 3:7</a></p>\n<h2>The grace and mercy of Jesus Christ and the Christian life</h2>\n<h3>The need to rely upon the grace of Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor12:9\">2CO 12:9</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:1\">2TI 2:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:7\">EPH 4:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:18\">2PE 3:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:16\">HEB 4:16</a></p>\n<h3>Prayers for the grace of Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:7\">ROM 1:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom16:20\">ROM 16:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor16:23\">1CO 16:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal1:3\">GAL 1:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:18\">GAL 6:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:24\">EPH 6:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil4:23\">PHP 4:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2John1:3\">2JN 1:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:21\">REV 22:21</a></p>",
